('world-cup-2026-african-qualification-race', '2026 World Cup: African qualification race heats up as Morocco lead the way', 'Nine automatic spots up for grabs with Egypt, Algeria, Senegal, and Nigeria in the hunt.', 'With Morocco already qualified, the race for Africa''s remaining eight automatic World Cup spots intensifies. Egypt and Algeria have strengthened their bids, while Nigeria face a tougher path. The expanded 48-team tournament offers a record nine places for African nations, with the best-placed runners-up entering intercontinental play-offs for a potential tenth berth. Ghana and other contenders will battle in the final qualifying matchdays.', 'transfer_rumour', true, '2026 World Cup Africa qualification', '2026-02-08 09:00:00')
